# Quest: Avalon Discord Bot

A fully-featured Discord bot that lets players run Quest: Avalon (4–10 players) entirely through Discord — roles are delivered via DM, all voting is done with buttons, and game state is managed per-channel.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> You need a **Discord Bot Token** before this can run. The bot token goes in a `.env` file (instructions in `README.md`). You'll also need to invite the bot with `applications.commands` and `bot` OAuth2 scopes.

> [!NOTE]
> The bot supports games from **4 to 10 players**. Multiple simultaneous games can run in different channels. All sensitive info (roles, loyalties) is sent via **private DM** — players must have DMs open from server members.

---

## Proposed Changes

### New Project: `quest_bg/`

---

#### [NEW] `quest_bg/bot.py`
Main bot entry point. Registers all slash commands and wires up Discord events.

**Slash commands:**
| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `/quest new` | Start a new game lobby in this channel |
| `/quest join` | Join the lobby |
| `/quest start` | Start the game (host only, 4–10 players) |
| `/quest pick @player1 @player2 ...` | Leader picks team members |
| `/quest seal @player` | Leader applies Magic Seal to a player |
| `/quest vote success/fail` | Mission team member submits quest card (via DM button) |
| `/quest accuse @p1 @p2` | Final Chance accusation (Good side only) |
| `/quest hunt role1 @player1 role2 @player2` | Blind Hunter reveals two Good players |
| `/quest status` | Show current game state |
| `/quest cancel` | Cancel the current game (host only) |

**Phase transitions are handled automatically** after each command.

---

#### [NEW] `quest_bg/game_state.py`
Core state machine for a single game instance. Stored in-memory per channel.

**Key classes:**
- `GameState` — holds all player/role/mission data
- `Phase` (enum) — `LOBBY`, `ROLE_REVEAL`, `TEAM_BUILD`, `QUEST`, `TRANSITION`, `DISCUSSION`, `FINAL_MISSION`, `HUNT`, `LAST_CHANCE`, `ENDED`

**Core logic:**
- Role assignment (shuffle + deal per player count chart)
- Night-phase reveal logic (who knows whom, based on role)
- Mission size table (4–10 players × 5 missions)
- Magic Seal enforcement
- Veteran token tracking (no player leads twice)
- Amulet placement (6+ players: between missions 2/3, 3/4, 4/5)
- Amulet loyalty check mechanic
- Mission result scoring (track success/fail markers)
- Q4 double-fail rule (7+ players)
- Last Chance vote logic
- Blind Hunter hunt logic
- Win condition checking after each mission

---

#### [NEW] `quest_bg/roles.py`
All role definitions with their constraints and special abilities.

**Roles (standard + optional):**

| Role | Side | Key Rule |
|---|---|---|
| Loyal Servant of Arthur | Good | Must play Success |
| Duke | Good | Redirect one hand in Last Chance |
| Archduke | Good | Swap one hand in Last Chance |
| Apprentice | Good | Raises one hand; second after Evil lowers |
| Cleric | Good | Knows if first Leader is Evil |
| Youth | Good | Must Fail if Magic Seal placed on them |
| Troublemaker | Good | Must lie Evil if loyalty-checked |
| Minion of Mordred | Evil | Knows other named Evil |
| Morgan le Fey | Evil | Bypasses Magic Seal; knows Scion |
| Scion | Evil (4–5p) | Unknown to other Evil |
| Changeling | Evil (6+p) | Unknown to everyone including Evil |
| Blind Hunter | Evil | Can Hunt: name 2 Good by role |
| Brute | Evil | Can only Fail in first 3 missions |
| Lunatic | Evil | Must always Fail (unless Magic Seal) |
| Mutineer | Evil | Can refuse to lower hand; can switch sides |
| Trickster | Evil | Can lie when loyalty-checked |
| Revealer | Evil | Must reveal after 3rd failed mission |
| Arthur | Good | Knows Morgan le Fey; if named first in Hunt, Evil wins |

---

#### [NEW] `quest_bg/views.py`
Discord UI button components for voting.

- `QuestVoteView` — Success/Fail buttons (DM to each team member)
- `LastChanceView` — Good-side accusation UI

---

#### [NEW] `quest_bg/embeds.py`
Embed helpers for consistent rich formatting.

---

